create 2 folder 1.zookeeper-logs for storing logs and 2. logs folder to store kafka logs

point these 2 folders to config folder inside server config file and zookeeper property files.


1. create log folder of logs and zookeeperlogs  and put the path inside config folder server  and zookeeper prop file


2. start the zookeeper (zookeeper-server-start.bat and zookeeper.prop file)

     .\bin\windows\zookeeper-server-start.bat .\config\zookeeper.properties

3. start server
	.\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat .\config\server.properties

4. create the topic

in bin windows
        kafka-topics.bat --create --topic quickstart-events --bootstrap-server localhost:9092

5. produce a message

   kafka-console-producer.bat --topic quickstart-events --bootstrap-server localhost:9092

6. consume a message

  kafka-console-consumer.bat --topic quickstart-events --from-beginning --bootstrap-server localhost:9092


Note: Kafka server running in 9092 port
        zookeeper running in port 2181